main event: Two brilliant objects were observed performing maneuvers in the sky over Livermore, California on May 13, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were heading Northwest and traveling at a high rate of speed., They were reflecting a lot of sunlight and were very bright., A trail of gray vapor was left behind as they maneuvered., Observers mentioned that the objects were smaller than known celestial objects but moved much faster., The conclusion of the report was that the objects were unidentified.
witness description: Observed the objects from a distance and noted their high speed and maneuvers.
